originalText.text: They are very professional. Prompt, courteous, and thoughtful. The move to get my baby grand up a tight stairway to the third floor was not an easy job. The Pianoland crew made it look so easy and smooth. They actually made a special trip to come check out the stairs before the day of the move. That's why the actual move was so successful and fast. I would definitely recommend these NYC Piano movers to anyone who needs to move their piano. You're not going to find anyone more experienced and professional.

originalText.text: When I needed piano movers to get an antique piano out of a New York loft, I called several piano moving companies. I was very impressed by the experience that was conveyed to me by the person from Pianoland. I hired them for the job and it went extremely well. They needed to partially disassemble it to navigate the stairwell that led to what was an old freight elevator. It was delivered to my shop in SoHo where it awaits its new owner. Once sold I will hire Pianoland again to move it.

originalText.text: My daughter needed a piano but a new one was not in our budget. I found a nice Yamaha on Craigslist, outside NYC in Brooklyn. I purchased it and hired Pianoland to do the piano moving for me. They are the professionals and I would never attempt it myself. They charge a flat rate from borough to borough which was very reasonable. They used great care in wrapping and loading it and delivering it to our Manhattan, New York apartment. My daughter loves her new piano.

originalText.text: When we moved to New Jersey from Staten Island, New York I would only trust Pianoland to move my Steinway. The regular movers said they would do it but I insisted on Pianoland because they are the NYC piano moving pro’s. The baby grand was delivered and set up in our great room in our new home where it will be played every day. Pianoland did a great job as expected.

originalText.text: We used Alex when we first got our piano and we were very pleased with the results.  We just moved and our movers damaged many of the keys during the move.  We called Alex again, and thank goodness, he managed to fix the keys and tune our piano so our daughter can once again play.  We were very pleased with his professionalism and skill and we highly recommend him to anyone that needs a piano moved and tuned.
